definition: irradiation is a process by which a material entity is exposed to radiative energy, which could be ionizing radiation (such as gamma rays or X-rays)  or not such as UV light or microwaves

studies.description: Transcriptional profiling of human lymphoblastoid TK6 cells comparing mock irradiated cells with cells exposed 24 hours previously to 1.67 Gy HZE (1 GeV/amu iron ions accelerated at the NASA Space Research Laboratory (NSRL) of Brookhaven National Laboratory) or 2.5 Gy 137Cs gamma rays. TK6 cells were mock irradiated or exposed to HZE or gamma-rays, and RNA was harvested 24 hours later. 3 biological replicates were independently grown and harvested during three different runs at the NSRL. One replicate per array.

protocols.description: HZE particle irradiation was performed at the NASA Space Radiation Laboratory (NSRL) at Brookhaven National Laboratory. Exponentially growing cells were concentrated by centrifugation and exposed to graded doses of 1 GeV/amu 56Fe ions (150 keV/μm) in a volume of 10 ml per culture point to limit the amount of medium activated during the irradiation. Dosimetry was performed by the NSRL Physics Group. Tubes containing the cells were placed perpendicular to the beam in the center of the field, where the variation in fluence was <5%. Control cultures were prepared in the same way and mock irradiated. An activated-medium control was prepared by irradiating 10 ml of medium without cells to the highest dose used (2.5 Gy). Immediately after irradiation, medium was added to bring the cells to normal culture densities (4-5 x 105cells/ml). Gamma-ray irradiation was performed at Columbia University using an AECL Gammacell-40 137Cs irradiator with a dose rate of 1.1 Gy/min.

protocols.description: RNA was extracted using a modified guanidine thiocyanate method, (Chomczynski and Sacchi, 1987, PMID: 2440339) followed by purification with RNeasy columns (Qiagen, Valencia, CA). RNA samples were quantified using a Nanodrop spectrophotometer and monitored for quality using an Agilent Bioanalyzer prior to labeling for microarray analysis.

protocols.description: 24 hours after treatment, fluorescently labeled cDNA was prepared from mock-irradiated control and irradiated whole-cell RNA by a single round of reverse transcription (BRL Superscript II) in the presence of aminoallyl dUTP (Sigma-Aldrich), followed by coupling to monofunctional NHS-ester Cy3 or Cy5 dye (Amersham) (Amundson and Fornace, 2004.
